# Next.js â€” Project Conventions

This is the **Next.js 16 Pages Router** frontend in the Tripteki parallel-codebase family. It pairs with NestJS, FastAPI, or Laravel backends via a shared REST contract.

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 Pages Router + React 19 + TypeScript |
| Dev server | `npm run dev` (Turbopack); clears `public/.next` before start |
| Auth | NextAuth.js 4 â€” Credentials provider, JWT session strategy |
| State | Redux Toolkit (`src/stores/`) |
| UI | Tailwind CSS 4 + Flowbite (`@tailwindcss/postcss`) |
| i18n | next-i18next â€” locales `en`, `id`, `ms`; cookie-based; **no URL prefix** |
| HTTP | axios |
| Forms | react-hook-form + zod |
| Realtime | Laravel Echo/Reverb **or** Socket.IO (driver switchable) |
| PWA | Manual `public/sw.js` + manifest under `public/manifest/` |

## Directory layout

```
pages/                  # Routes + API routes only (thin wiring)
  api/auth/             # NextAuth handler
  api/webpush/          # Web Push subscription
  *.page.tsx            # SSR pages (default build)
  *.static.tsx          # Static-export pages (BUILD_STATIC=true)
src/
  components/           # UI (kebab-case files)
  components/flowbite/  # Fb* wrappers (fb-button, fb-input, â€¦)
  hooks/                # use-*.ts custom hooks
  layouts/              # *.layout.tsx
  libs/                 # Shared utilities (auth, API, realtime, flowbite-classes)
  styles/               # globals.css, brand-theme.css
  stores/               # Redux slices
  types/                # Shared TypeScript types
  page-auth/            # Per-route auth metadata consumed by proxy.ts
  langs/                # Translation JSON
tests/lib/              # Vitest unit tests
tests/e2e/              # Playwright e2e tests
proxy.ts                # Route guard (Next 16 â€” NOT middleware.ts)
```

**Rule:** Keep `pages/` thin. Business logic, components, and hooks live in `src/`.

## Dual build system

- **SSR (default):** pages named `*.page.tsx` â†’ `npm run build` â†’ output in `public/.next` (custom `distDir`)
- **Static export:** pages named `*.static.tsx` â†’ `BUILD_STATIC=true npm run generate` â†’ `out/`
- Do not mix `.page.tsx` and `.static.tsx` for the same route

## Authentication & route protection

### Server-side (`proxy.ts`)
- Next.js 16 uses **`proxy.ts`** for edge route guards
- **Never create `middleware.ts`** â€” it conflicts with `proxy.ts` and breaks auth redirects
- `proxy.ts` reads auth metadata from `src/page-auth/` modules

### Session validation
- `hasValidSession()` in `src/libs/auth-session.ts` requires a non-empty **access token**, not just `status === "authenticated"`
- Logout must call `POST /api/auth/logout` to clear cookies server-side
- After logout, dashboard and protected routes must redirect to login

### getServerSideProps
- Always use `buildGetServerSideProps()` from `src/libs/page-props.server.ts`
- Include `serverSideTranslations` for i18n on every SSR page
- Serialize session props: use `null` for missing values â€” **never `undefined`** (Next.js GSSP serialization error)
- Session callback must set `session.error` to `null` (not `undefined`) when there is no error

### Client-side guards
- `useRequireAuth()` â€” redirect unauthenticated users
- `useRequireGuest()` â€” redirect authenticated users away from login/register

## Environment variables

| Variable | Scope | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL` | Public | Frontend origin |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | Public | Backend REST base |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH_URL` | Public | Auth API base |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_DRIVER` | Public | `echo` or `socketio` |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_REVERB_*` | Public | Laravel Reverb/Echo config |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY` | Public | Web Push |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` | Public | `development` / `production` |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_LANG` | Public | Default locale |
| `NEXTAUTH_URL` | Server | NextAuth callback URL |
| `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` | Server | Session encryption |
| `SECRET` | Server | App secret |

- Read runtime config via `src/libs/runtime-config.ts` â€” do not scatter `process.env` reads
- `.env.example` uses `api.backend.localhost`; local `.env` may use `localhost:8000`

## Testing

```bash
npm test              # Vitest unit tests (tests/lib/**/*.test.ts)
npm run test:watch  # Vitest watch mode
npm run test:e2e    # Playwright (tests/e2e/, uses data-test selectors)
npm run test:e2e:ui # Playwright UI mode
```

- E2E base URL from `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`
- Default e2e credentials: `user@mail.com` / `12345678`

## Code style

- **Files:** kebab-case (`theme-toggle.tsx`, `use-notifications.ts`)
- **Imports:** `@/components/*`, `@/hooks/*`, `@/libs/*` (no file extension)
- **Formatting:** Allman braces, spaces inside parentheses `( foo, bar )` â€” `@tripteki/prettier-config`
- **Lint:** `npm run lint` (eslint-config-next + prettier)

## UI conventions (Flowbite)

- **CSS:** `src/styles/globals.css` imports Flowbite plugin; brand utilities in `src/styles/brand-theme.css`
- **Class tokens:** `src/libs/flowbite-classes.ts` â€” prefer `fbCard`, `fbMuted`, `fbAlert*` over ad-hoc gray classes
- **Components:** use `src/components/flowbite/fb-*.tsx`; dropdowns/modals are custom React, not Flowbite JS widgets
- **Plugins:** `fb-apex-chart`, `fb-data-table`, `fb-wysiwyg` + `src/libs/flowbite-chart-options.ts`
- **Init:** `initFlowbite()` in `src/app-shell.tsx` on route changes
- **Header action order (left â†’ right in actions area):** i18n switcher â†’ theme toggle â†’ notifications â†’ avatar/profile â†’ logout
- **Buttons:** loading state uses `gap-2` between `FbSpinner` and label
- **Alerts:** use `AlertSuccess`, `AlertWarning`, `AlertError` â€” flex layout with `mb-4` spacing
